---
import Layout from "../../layouts/layout.astro";
import Container from "../../components/container/container.astro";
import Heading from "../../components/heading/heading.astro";
import styles from "../_styles/content-page.module.css";
---

<Layout
  title="OBS Overlay Guide - Guilty Spark"
  description="Step-by-step setup guide for Guilty Spark overlays in OBS for both live tracker and Individual Tracker workflows."
>
  <section class={styles.contentPage}>
    <Container>
      <header class={styles.heroBlock}>
        <p class={styles.eyebrow}>Field Guide</p>
        <Heading tagName="h1" class={styles.title}>OBS Overlay Setup</Heading>
        <p class={styles.subtitle}>
          Use this guide to deploy Guilty Spark overlays in OBS from either live series tracker mode or individual
          tracker mode.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class={styles.section} aria-label="Live tracker to OBS flow">
        <div class={styles.card}>
          <h3>Flow A: Live Tracker to OBS</h3>
          <ol class={styles.steps}>
            <li>Open a live tracker session and verify the series context is active.</li>
            <li>Open overlay settings and switch to Streamer Overlay mode.</li>
            <li>Copy the generated URL.</li>
            <li>In OBS, add a Browser Source and paste the URL.</li>
            <li>Set dimensions to 1920x1080, then resize in-scene as needed.</li>
          </ol>
          <figure class={styles.mediaItem}>
            <img
              src="/images/faq/tracker-step-1-live-tracker.png"
              alt="Live tracker page with active series overview"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              Reference: live tracker view showing active series context before opening overlay settings.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class={styles.mediaItem}>
            <img
              src="/images/faq/tracker-step-3-streamer-and-copy-url.png"
              alt="Overlay settings showing Copy URL for OBS in streamer mode"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>Reference: copy the generated OBS URL from streamer overlay mode.</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class={styles.mediaItem}>
            <img
              src="/images/faq/obs-step-1-browser-source-settings.png"
              alt="OBS Browser Source settings for Guilty Spark overlay"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>Reference: Browser Source setup in OBS for live tracker overlays.</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class={styles.section} aria-label="Individual tracker to OBS flow">
        <div class={styles.card}>
          <h3>Flow B: Individual Tracker to OBS</h3>
          <ol class={styles.steps}>
            <li>Open Individual Tracker manager and select the tracker to broadcast.</li>
            <li>Open tracker overlay settings and copy the OBS URL.</li>
            <li>Create or update a Browser Source in OBS with the copied URL.</li>
            <li>Confirm tabs, ticker, and stat regions are readable in preview.</li>
            <li>Lock the source in OBS once layout is final.</li>
          </ol>
          <figure class={styles.mediaItem}>
            <img
              src="/images/content-refresh/faq-individual-step-1-open-tracker.svg"
              alt="Requested screenshot placeholder for opening the Individual Tracker manager"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>Requested asset: tracker manager view with active tracker cards and controls.</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class={styles.mediaItem}>
            <img
              src="/images/content-refresh/faq-individual-step-2-copy-overlay-url.svg"
              alt="Requested screenshot placeholder for copying Individual Tracker overlay URL"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              Requested asset: tracker overlay settings panel with Copy URL for OBS action visible.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class={styles.mediaItem}>
            <img
              src="/images/content-refresh/faq-individual-step-3-obs-preview.svg"
              alt="Requested screenshot placeholder for OBS preview with Individual Tracker overlay"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              Requested asset: final OBS preview or program output with Individual Tracker overlay enabled.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class={styles.section} aria-label="Troubleshooting">
        <div class={styles.card}>
          <h3>Troubleshooting and Performance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>If content appears stale, use Refresh cache of current page in Browser Source properties.</li>
            <li>Lower Browser Source resolution for low-resource stream profiles.</li>
            <li>If text appears cropped, check scene scaling and browser source bounds.</li>
            <li>Keep only one active source per overlay URL to avoid confusion during live edits.</li>
          </ul>
          <figure class={styles.mediaItem}>
            <img
              src="/images/content-refresh/guides-obs-flow-request.svg"
              alt="Requested media placeholder for end-to-end OBS setup flow"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              Requested asset: replace with a short GIF or MP4 showing copy URL, Browser Source setup, and final preview
              in OBS.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </section>
    </Container>
  </section>
</Layout>
